#fatstudios
Sümela Monastery is a 1600-year-old Orthodox #mountaintop #monastery, built on the side of Karadağ Mountain, which is located in the Altındağ Valley of #Trabzon’s #Maçka district.
Currently included in UNESCO’s Tentative List of World #Heritage Sites in #Turkey, this religious complex is presumed to have been built in the 4th century AD during the reign of the #Byzantine Emperor Theodosius I, by two priests named Barnabas and Sophronios who were natives to Athens, Greece. 
-
📸: @fatihmorguel, @cemilsahin, @enghasanali 

Today, Sümela monastery is, perhaps, the most popular tourist attraction in Turkey’s #BlackSea region. And with its amazingly well-preserved artistic frescoes and stunning architectural features and location, this magical site is deserving of its admiration. 
-
#turkey #türkiye #turkiye #turkey🇹🇷 #architecture #ancient #unescoworldheritagesite #unescoworldheritage
